  ggplot()+

  scale_x_discrete(guide = guide_axis(angle = 0),labels = function(x) str_wrap(x, width = 7))+

# how long it took each treatment to die
time_to_death <- combined %>%
  filter(end_status == "dead") %>%
  ggplot(aes(x=splits, y = days_to_event, color = splits))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_boxplot()
time_to_death

This is a density graph showing the time until cocoon completion (only showing bees that survived). The development time of control bees is overlayed onto each other treatment.

  filter(end_status=="cocoon")%>%
  ggplot(aes(x=treatment, y=days_to_event, color = treatment))+
  geom_boxplot()+ 
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, vjust = 0.5, hjust=1))+
  theme_bw()

Here higher percent empty corrected (y axis) indicated better digestion ability

so antibiotics dont interfere with digestion ability but sterilization or pollen switching does. Re-addition of (some) microbes to pollen provision does not negate these impacts.
